{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":373,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Commissioner,\nthank you for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3196,"text":"Ant√≥nio Guterres: Pleasure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4537,"text":"BG: Let's start with a figure."},{"time":6013,"text":"During 2015, almost one million refugees\nand migrants arrived in Europe"},{"time":10178,"text":"from many different countries,"},{"time":11677,"text":"of course, from Syria and Iraq,\nbut also from Afghanistan"},{"time":14399,"text":"and Bangladesh and Eritrea and elsewhere."},{"time":16885,"text":"And there have been reactions\nof two different kinds:"},{"time":19409,"text":"welcoming parties and border fences."},{"time":23148,"text":"But I want to look at it a little bit"},{"time":25229,"text":"from the short-term\nand the long-term perspective."},{"time":28083,"text":"And the first question is very simple:"},{"time":31599,"text":"Why has the movement of refugees\nspiked so fast in the last six months?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":36091,"text":"AG: Well, I think, basically,\nwhat triggered this huge increase"},{"time":39408,"text":"was the Syrian refugee group."},{"time":41353,"text":"There has been an increased movement\ninto Europe from Africa, from Asia,"},{"time":46113,"text":"but slowly growing, and all of a sudden\nwe had this massive increase"},{"time":49963,"text":"in the first months of this year."},{"time":52421,"text":"Why? I think there are three reasons,"},{"time":54313,"text":"two long-term ones and the trigger."},{"time":56370,"text":"The long-term ones,\nin relation to Syrians,"},{"time":58942,"text":"is that hope is less and less\nclear for people."},{"time":65573,"text":"I mean, they look at their own country"},{"time":67629,"text":"and they don't see much hope\nto go back home,"},{"time":70334,"text":"because there is no political solution,"},{"time":72303,"text":"so there is no light\nat the end of the tunnel."},{"time":75382,"text":"Second, the living conditions"},{"time":77030,"text":"of the Syrians in the neighboring\ncountries have been deteriorating."},{"time":80380,"text":"We just had research with the World Bank,"},{"time":82657,"text":"and 87 percent of the Syrians in Jordan"},{"time":87017,"text":"and 93 percent of the Syrians in Lebanon"},{"time":89942,"text":"live below the national poverty lines."},{"time":92828,"text":"Only half of the children go to school,"},{"time":95785,"text":"which means that people\nare living very badly."},{"time":98831,"text":"Not only are they refugees, out of home,"},{"time":100779,"text":"not only have they suffered\nwhat they have suffered,"},{"time":103255,"text":"but they are living in very,\nvery dramatic conditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105848,"text":"And then the trigger\nwas when all of a sudden,"},{"time":108192,"text":"international aid decreased."},{"time":109919,"text":"The World Food Programme was forced,\nfor lack of resources,"},{"time":112736,"text":"to cut by 30 percent food support\nto the Syrian refugees."},{"time":115824,"text":"They're not allowed to work,"},{"time":117271,"text":"so they are totally dependent\non international support,"},{"time":120823,"text":"and they felt, \"The world\nis abandoning us.\""},{"time":123151,"text":"And that, in my opinion, was the trigger."},{"time":125135,"text":"All of a sudden, there was a rush,"},{"time":126794,"text":"and people started to move\nin large numbers"},{"time":128833,"text":"and, to be absolutely honest,"},{"time":130415,"text":"if I had been in the same situation"},{"time":132638,"text":"and I would have been brave\nenough to do it,"},{"time":134769,"text":"I think I would have done the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136496,"text":"BG: But I think what surprised\nmany people is it's not only sudden,"},{"time":140785,"text":"but it wasn't supposed to be sudden."},{"time":143009,"text":"The war in Syria has been\nhappening for five years."},{"time":145446,"text":"Millions of refugees are in camps\nand villages and towns around Syria."},{"time":149130,"text":"You have yourself warned\nabout the situation"},{"time":151534,"text":"and about the consequences\nof a breakdown of Libya, for example,"},{"time":154841,"text":"and yet Europe looked totally unprepared."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158618,"text":"AG: Well, unprepared because divided,"},{"time":161101,"text":"and when you are divided,\nyou don't want to recognize the reality."},{"time":164403,"text":"You prefer to postpone decisions,"},{"time":166284,"text":"because you do not have\nthe capacity to make them."},{"time":168744,"text":"And the proof is that even when\nthe spike occurred,"},{"time":172230,"text":"Europe remained divided"},{"time":173557,"text":"and was unable to put in place\na mechanism to manage the situation."},{"time":179250,"text":"You talk about one million people."},{"time":180965,"text":"It looks enormous,"},{"time":182560,"text":"but the population of the European Union\nis 550 million people,"},{"time":187084,"text":"which means we are talking about one\nper every [550] Europeans."},{"time":191473,"text":"Now, in Lebanon, we have one refugee\nper three Lebanese."},{"time":195426,"text":"And Lebanon? Struggling,\nof course, but it's managing."},{"time":199681,"text":"So, the question is: is this something\nthat could have been managed"},{"time":203971,"text":"if -- not mentioning the most\nimportant thing,"},{"time":207016,"text":"which would have been\naddressing the root causes,"},{"time":209412,"text":"but forgetting about root causes for now,"},{"time":211412,"text":"looking at the phenomenon as it is --"},{"time":213261,"text":"if Europe were able to come\ntogether in solidarity"},{"time":217575,"text":"to create an adequate\nreception capacity of entry points?"},{"time":221739,"text":"But for that, the countries at entry\npoints need to be massively supported,"},{"time":226447,"text":"and then screening the people\nwith security checks"},{"time":229476,"text":"and all the other mechanisms,"},{"time":230905,"text":"distributing those that are coming\ninto all European countries,"},{"time":234434,"text":"according to the possibilities\nof each country."},{"time":236691,"text":"I mean, if you look at\nthe relocation program"},{"time":238991,"text":"that was approved by the Commission,\nalways too little too late,"},{"time":242078,"text":"or by the Council, too little too late --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244024,"text":"BG: It's already breaking down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245533,"text":"AG: My country is supposed\nto receive four thousand."},{"time":248014,"text":"Four thousand in Portugal means nothing."},{"time":250045,"text":"So this is perfectly manageable\nif it is managed,"},{"time":253838,"text":"but in the present circumstances,\nthe pressure is at the point of entry,"},{"time":257272,"text":"and then, as people move\nin this chaotic way through the Balkans,"},{"time":260755,"text":"then they come to Germany,\nSweden, basically, and Austria."},{"time":264125,"text":"They are the three countries that are,\nin the end, receiving the refugees."},{"time":267655,"text":"The rest of Europe is looking\nwithout doing much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270211,"text":"BG: Let me try to bring up\nthree questions,"},{"time":272594,"text":"playing a bit devil's advocate."},{"time":274115,"text":"I'll try to ask them, make them blunt."},{"time":277061,"text":"But I think the questions are very present"},{"time":279124,"text":"in the minds of many people\nin Europe right now,"},{"time":281401,"text":"The first, of course, is about numbers."},{"time":283356,"text":"You say 550 million versus one million\nis not much, but realistically,"},{"time":288186,"text":"how many people can Europe take?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":290160,"text":"AG: Well, that is a question\nthat has no answer,"},{"time":293696,"text":"because refugees have\nthe right to be protected."},{"time":297947,"text":"And there is such a thing\nas international law,"},{"time":301138,"text":"so there is no way you can say,\n\"I take 10,000 and that's finished.\""},{"time":305531,"text":"I remind you of one thing:"},{"time":307342,"text":"in Turkey, at the beginning of the crisis,\nI remember one minister saying,"},{"time":311242,"text":"\"Turkey will be able to receive\nup to 100,000 people.\""},{"time":314241,"text":"Turkey has now two million\nthree-hundred thousand"},{"time":317710,"text":"or something of the sort,\nif you count all refugees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320182,"text":"So I don't think it's fair to say\nhow many we can take."},{"time":324395,"text":"What it is fair to say is:\nhow we can we organize ourselves"},{"time":327965,"text":"to assume our international\nresponsibilities?"},{"time":330734,"text":"And Europe has not been able to do so,"},{"time":333208,"text":"because basically, Europe is divided\nbecause there is no solidarity"},{"time":336783,"text":"in the European project."},{"time":337986,"text":"And it's not only about refugees;\nthere are many other areas."},{"time":341136,"text":"And let's be honest, this is the moment\nin which we need more Europe"},{"time":344794,"text":"instead of less Europe."},{"time":346354,"text":"But as the public less and less believes\nin European institutions,"},{"time":350997,"text":"it is also each time more difficult\nto convince the public"},{"time":354303,"text":"that we need more Europe\nto solve these problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356629,"text":"BG: We seem to be at the point"},{"time":358100,"text":"where the numbers turn into political\nshifts, particularly domestically."},{"time":361535,"text":"We saw it again this weekend in France,"},{"time":363431,"text":"but we have seen it over\nand over in many countries:"},{"time":365907,"text":"in Poland and in Denmark\nand in Switzerland and elsewhere,"},{"time":368664,"text":"where the mood changes radically\nbecause of the numbers,"},{"time":372237,"text":"although they are not very significant\nin absolute numbers."},{"time":378471,"text":"The Prime Minister of --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":380548,"text":"AG: But, if I may, on these:"},{"time":382294,"text":"I mean, what does a European see at home"},{"time":385619,"text":"in a village where there are no migrants?"},{"time":388239,"text":"What a European sees is, on television,"},{"time":392891,"text":"every single day, a few months ago,\nopening the news every single day,"},{"time":397315,"text":"a crowd coming, uncontrolled,"},{"time":399777,"text":"moving from border to border,"},{"time":401541,"text":"and the images on television\nwere of hundreds"},{"time":403745,"text":"or thousands of people moving."},{"time":405436,"text":"And the idea is that nobody\nis taking care of it --"},{"time":408640,"text":"this is happening without any\nkind of management."},{"time":412013,"text":"And so their idea was,\n\"They are coming to my village.\""},{"time":414862,"text":"So there was this completely false idea\nthat Europe was being invaded"},{"time":418959,"text":"and our way of life is going to change,\nand everything will --"},{"time":422744,"text":"And the problem is that if this\nhad been properly managed,"},{"time":426633,"text":"if people had been properly received,"},{"time":428519,"text":"welcomed, sheltered at point of entry,\nscreened at point of entry,"},{"time":433258,"text":"and the moved by plane\nto different European countries,"},{"time":435971,"text":"this would not have scared people."},{"time":438153,"text":"But, unfortunately, we have\na lot of people scared,"},{"time":440820,"text":"just because Europe was not able\nto do the job properly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443867,"text":"BG: But there are villages in Germany"},{"time":445883,"text":"with 300 inhabitants and 1,000 refugees."},{"time":449243,"text":"So, what's your position?"},{"time":451241,"text":"How do you imagine these people reacting?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453232,"text":"AG: If there would be a proper\nmanagement of the situation"},{"time":456129,"text":"and the proper distribution\nof people all over Europe,"},{"time":459233,"text":"you would always have\nthe percentage that I mentioned:"},{"time":462233,"text":"one per each 2,000."},{"time":464059,"text":"It is because things are not\nproperly managed"},{"time":466352,"text":"that in the end we have situations"},{"time":468136,"text":"that are totally impossible to live with,\nand of course if you have a village --"},{"time":474577,"text":"in Lebanon, there are many villages"},{"time":476278,"text":"that have more Syrians than Lebanese;\nLebanon has been living with that."},{"time":479710,"text":"I'm not asking for the same\nto happen in Europe,"},{"time":482001,"text":"for all European villages to have\nmore refugees than inhabitants."},{"time":485212,"text":"What I am asking is for Europe\nto do the job properly,"},{"time":488291,"text":"and to be able to organize itself\nto receive people"},{"time":491736,"text":"as other countries in the world\nwere forced to do in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494688,"text":"BG: So, if you look at the global\nsituation not only at Europe --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":497776,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":499089,"text":"BG: Yes!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":500264,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":504922,"text":"BG: If you look at the global situation,\nso, not only at Europe,"},{"time":507967,"text":"I know you can make\na long list of countries"},{"time":510095,"text":"that are not really stepping up,"},{"time":513242,"text":"but I'm more interested\nin the other part --"},{"time":515714,"text":"is there somebody\nwho's doing the right thing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":518402,"text":"AG: Well, 86 percent\nof the refugees in the world"},{"time":520857,"text":"are in the developing world."},{"time":522936,"text":"And if you look at\ncountries like Ethiopia --"},{"time":526280,"text":"Ethiopia has received\nmore than 600,000 refugees."},{"time":530486,"text":"All the borders in Ethiopia are open."},{"time":533304,"text":"And they have, as a policy,"},{"time":535196,"text":"they call the \"people to people\" policy\nthat every refugee should be received."},{"time":539316,"text":"And they have South Sudanese,"},{"time":540919,"text":"they have Sudanese, they have Somalis."},{"time":542951,"text":"They have all the neighbors."},{"time":544832,"text":"They have Eritreans."},{"time":546929,"text":"And, in general,"},{"time":548248,"text":"African countries are extremely\nwelcoming of refugees coming,"},{"time":552452,"text":"and I would say that in the Middle East"},{"time":555048,"text":"and in Asia, we have seen a tendency\nfor borders to be open."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560265,"text":"Now we see some problems\nwith the Syrian situation,"},{"time":563654,"text":"as the Syrian situation evolved\ninto also a major security crisis,"},{"time":567935,"text":"but the truth is that for a large period,"},{"time":570052,"text":"all borders in the Middle East were open."},{"time":572068,"text":"The truth is that for Afghans,"},{"time":573544,"text":"the borders of Pakistan and Iran\nwere open for, at the time,"},{"time":576401,"text":"six million Afghans that came."},{"time":578318,"text":"So I would say that even today,\nthe trend in the developing world"},{"time":582163,"text":"has been for borders to be open."},{"time":584513,"text":"The trend in the developed world\nis for these questions to become"},{"time":588949,"text":"more and more complex,"},{"time":591079,"text":"especially when there is,\nin the public opinion,"},{"time":593674,"text":"a mixture of discussions between refugee\nprotections on one side"},{"time":598781,"text":"and security questions -- in my opinion,\nmisinterpreted -- on the other side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602444,"text":"BG: We'll come back to that too,"},{"time":604009,"text":"but you mentioned the cutting\nof funding and the vouchers"},{"time":606773,"text":"from the World Food Programme."},{"time":608257,"text":"That reflects the general underfunding\nof the organizations"},{"time":611114,"text":"working on these issues."},{"time":614155,"text":"Now that the world seems to have woken up,"},{"time":616734,"text":"are you getting more funding\nand more support,"},{"time":618949,"text":"or it's still the same?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":620386,"text":"AG: We are getting more support."},{"time":622209,"text":"I would say that we are coming\nclose to the levels of last year."},{"time":627100,"text":"We were much worse during the summer."},{"time":629799,"text":"But that is clearly insufficient\nto address the needs of the people"},{"time":633681,"text":"and address the needs of the countries"},{"time":635595,"text":"that are supporting the people."},{"time":637118,"text":"And here we have a basic review\nof the criteria, the objectives,"},{"time":643068,"text":"the priorities of development\ncooperation that is required."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645884,"text":"For instance, Lebanon and Jordan\nare middle-income countries."},{"time":648911,"text":"Because they are middle-income countries,"},{"time":650909,"text":"they cannot receive soft loans\nor grants from the World Bank."},{"time":653844,"text":"Now, today this doesn't make any sense,"},{"time":656067,"text":"because they are providing\na global public good."},{"time":658420,"text":"They have millions of refugees there,"},{"time":660254,"text":"and to be honest, they are pillars\nof stability in the region,"},{"time":663768,"text":"with all the difficulties they face,"},{"time":665530,"text":"and the first line of defense\nof our collective security."},{"time":668244,"text":"So it doesn't make sense"},{"time":669431,"text":"that these countries\nare not a first priority"},{"time":671598,"text":"in development cooperation policies."},{"time":673367,"text":"And they are not."},{"time":674550,"text":"And not only do the refugees live\nin very dramatic circumstances"},{"time":677976,"text":"inside those countries,"},{"time":679230,"text":"but the local communities\nthemselves are suffering,"},{"time":682080,"text":"because salaries went down,"},{"time":685491,"text":"because there are more unemployed,"},{"time":687162,"text":"because prices and rents went up."},{"time":690238,"text":"And, of course, if you look\nat today's situation"},{"time":694206,"text":"of the indicators in these countries,"},{"time":697328,"text":"it is clear that, especially\ntheir poor groups of the population,"},{"time":702835,"text":"are living worse and worse\nbecause of the crisis they are facing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706094,"text":"BG: Who should be providing this support?"},{"time":708102,"text":"Country by country, international\norganizations, the European Union?"},{"time":711447,"text":"Who should be coming up with this support?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":713519,"text":"AG: We need to join all efforts."},{"time":715088,"text":"It's clear that bilateral\ncooperation is essential."},{"time":717657,"text":"It's clear that multilateral\ncooperation is essential."},{"time":720444,"text":"It's clear that international financial\ninstitutions should have flexibility"},{"time":724063,"text":"in order to be able to invest\nmore massively"},{"time":726806,"text":"in support to these countries."},{"time":728356,"text":"We need to combine all the instruments\nand to understand that today,"},{"time":731626,"text":"in protracted situations,\nat a certain moment,"},{"time":734096,"text":"that it doesn't make sense anymore\nto make a distinction"},{"time":736790,"text":"between humanitarian aid\nand development aid"},{"time":740463,"text":"or development processes."},{"time":742836,"text":"Because you are talking\nabout children in school,"},{"time":746463,"text":"you are talking about health,"},{"time":747896,"text":"you are talking about infrastructure\nthat is overcrowded."},{"time":750752,"text":"You are talking about things\nthat require a long-term perspective,"},{"time":754345,"text":"a development perspective"},{"time":755702,"text":"and not only an emergency\nhumanitarian aid perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759147,"text":"BG: I would like your comment on something"},{"time":761195,"text":"that was in newspapers this morning."},{"time":762972,"text":"It is a statement made\nby the current front-runner"},{"time":768368,"text":"for the Republican nomination\nfor US President, Donald Trump."},{"time":771738,"text":"Yesterday, he said this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773128,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":774153,"text":"No, listen to this. It's interesting."},{"time":775969,"text":"I quote: \"I am calling for a total\nand complete shutdown"},{"time":778863,"text":"of Muslims entering the US,"},{"time":780585,"text":"until our country's representatives\ncan figure out what's going on.\""},{"time":785425,"text":"How do you react to that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":786808,"text":"AG: Well, it's not only Donald Trump."},{"time":788916,"text":"We have seen several people\naround the world"},{"time":791206,"text":"with political responsibility\nsaying, for instance,"},{"time":793643,"text":"that Muslims refugees\nshould not be received."},{"time":796108,"text":"And the reason why they say this"},{"time":799632,"text":"is because they think\nthat by doing or saying this,"},{"time":802755,"text":"they are protecting\nthe security of their countries."},{"time":805361,"text":"Now, I've been in government."},{"time":806818,"text":"I am very keen on the need for governments"},{"time":809120,"text":"to protect the security of their countries"},{"time":811589,"text":"and their people."},{"time":812764,"text":"But if you say, like that,"},{"time":815711,"text":"in the US or in any European country,"},{"time":818241,"text":"\"We are going to close our doors\nto Muslim refugees,\""},{"time":822211,"text":"what you are saying\nis the best possible help"},{"time":825347,"text":"for the propaganda\nof terrorist organizations."},{"time":828146,"text":"Because what you are saying --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":829782,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":835381,"text":"What you are saying will be heard\nby all the Muslims in your own country,"},{"time":840988,"text":"and it will pave the way\nfor the recruitment"},{"time":843085,"text":"and the mechanisms that,\nthrough technology,"},{"time":845730,"text":"Daesh and al-Nusra, al-Qaeda,\nand all those other groups"},{"time":849609,"text":"are today penetrating in our societies."},{"time":852031,"text":"And it's just telling them,\n\"You are right, we are against you.\""},{"time":856176,"text":"So obviously, this is creating\nin societies that are all multiethnic,"},{"time":862590,"text":"multi-religious, multicultural,"},{"time":864363,"text":"this is creating a situation\nin which, really,"},{"time":867759,"text":"it is much easier for the propaganda\nof these terrorist organizations"},{"time":871173,"text":"to be effective in recruiting\npeople for terror acts"},{"time":876310,"text":"within the countries where these kinds\nof sentences are expressed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880248,"text":"BG: Have the recent attacks in Paris\nand the reactions to them"},{"time":883255,"text":"made your job more difficult?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":885262,"text":"AG: Undoubtedly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886645,"text":"BG: In what sense?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":888992,"text":"AG: In the sense that, I mean,\nfor many people the first reaction"},{"time":893332,"text":"in relation to these kinds of terrorist\nattacks is: close all borders --"},{"time":896776,"text":"not understanding that the terrorist\nproblem in Europe is largely homegrown."},{"time":901245,"text":"We have thousands and thousands\nof European fighters in Syria and in Iraq,"},{"time":906242,"text":"so this is not something that you solve\nby just not allowing Syrians to come in."},{"time":910496,"text":"And I must say, I am convinced"},{"time":912976,"text":"that the passport that appeared,"},{"time":917172,"text":"I believe, was put\nby the person who has blown --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":920943,"text":"BG: -- himself up, yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922498,"text":"AG: [I believe] it was on purpose,"},{"time":924433,"text":"because part of the strategies\nof Daesh is against refugees,"},{"time":928075,"text":"because they see refugees as people\nthat should be with the caliphate"},{"time":931512,"text":"and are fleeing to the crusaders."},{"time":933988,"text":"And I think that is part of Daesh's\nstrategy to make Europe react,"},{"time":938075,"text":"closing its doors to Muslim refugees"},{"time":940490,"text":"and having an hostility\ntowards Muslims inside Europe,"},{"time":944205,"text":"exactly to facilitate Daesh's work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":947751,"text":"And my deep belief is that\nit was not the refugee movement"},{"time":952283,"text":"that triggered terrorism."},{"time":953988,"text":"I think, as I said,"},{"time":955172,"text":"essentially terrorism in Europe\nis today a homegrown movement"},{"time":958723,"text":"in relation to the global situation\nthat we are facing,"},{"time":962042,"text":"and what we need is exactly\nto prove these groups wrong,"},{"time":966486,"text":"by welcoming and integrating effectively"},{"time":969983,"text":"those that are coming\nfrom that part of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972410,"text":"And another thing that I believe\nis that to a large extent,"},{"time":975450,"text":"what we are today paying for in Europe"},{"time":977937,"text":"is the failures of integration models"},{"time":980131,"text":"that didn't work in the '60s,\nin the '70s, in the '80s,"},{"time":983296,"text":"in relation to big migration flows\nthat took place at that time"},{"time":986291,"text":"and generated what is today\nin many of the people, for instance,"},{"time":990104,"text":"of the second generation of communities,"},{"time":992871,"text":"a situation of feeling marginalized,"},{"time":997026,"text":"having no jobs,"},{"time":998440,"text":"having improper education,"},{"time":1000003,"text":"living in some of the neighborhoods\nthat are not adequately provided"},{"time":1005252,"text":"by public infrastructure."},{"time":1007518,"text":"And this kind of uneasiness,\nsometimes even anger,"},{"time":1012375,"text":"that exists in this second generation"},{"time":1014868,"text":"is largely due to the failure\nof integration policies,"},{"time":1017915,"text":"to the failure of what should have been\na much stronger investment"},{"time":1021820,"text":"in creating the conditions for people\nto live together and respect each other."},{"time":1026232,"text":"For me it is clear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027564,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030829,"text":"For me it is clear that all societies\nwill be multiethnic, multicultural,"},{"time":1034723,"text":"multi-religious in the future."},{"time":1036666,"text":"To try to avoid it is,\nin my opinion, impossible."},{"time":1040420,"text":"And for me it's a good thing\nthat they will be like that,"},{"time":1043344,"text":"but I also recognize that,\nfor that to work properly,"},{"time":1046746,"text":"you need a huge investment"},{"time":1048726,"text":"in the social cohesion\nof your own societies."},{"time":1051186,"text":"And Europe, to a large extent,\nfailed in that investment"},{"time":1054884,"text":"in the past few decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1058121,"text":"BG: Question: You are stepping down\nfrom your job at the end of the year,"},{"time":1062141,"text":"after 10 years."},{"time":1063698,"text":"If you look back at 2005,"},{"time":1065159,"text":"when you entered that office\nfor the first time, what do you see?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1069491,"text":"AG: Well, look:"},{"time":1072466,"text":"In 2005, we were helping\none million people go back home"},{"time":1077867,"text":"in safety and dignity,\nbecause conflicts had ended."},{"time":1081692,"text":"Last year, we helped 124,000."},{"time":1085659,"text":"In 2005, we had about 38 million people\ndisplaced by conflict in the world."},{"time":1090771,"text":"Today, we have more than 60 million."},{"time":1094052,"text":"At that time, we had had, recently,"},{"time":1097143,"text":"some conflicts that were solved."},{"time":1100393,"text":"Now, we see a multiplication\nof new conflicts"},{"time":1102724,"text":"and the old conflicts never died:"},{"time":1104589,"text":"Afghanistan, Somalia,\nDemocratic Republic of Congo."},{"time":1107969,"text":"It is clear that the world today\nis much more dangerous than it was."},{"time":1112049,"text":"It is clear that the capacity\nof the international community"},{"time":1114917,"text":"to prevent conflicts\nand to timely solve them,"},{"time":1117817,"text":"is, unfortunately, much worse\nthan what it was 10 years ago."},{"time":1121995,"text":"There are no clear\npower relations in the world,"},{"time":1124764,"text":"no global governance mechanisms that work,"},{"time":1127281,"text":"which means that we live in a situation"},{"time":1130084,"text":"where impunity and unpredictability\ntend to prevail, and that means"},{"time":1135034,"text":"that more and more people suffer,"},{"time":1137473,"text":"namely those that are\ndisplaced by conflicts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1139890,"text":"BG: It's a tradition in American politics"},{"time":1141920,"text":"that when a President leaves\nthe Oval Office for the last time,"},{"time":1145574,"text":"he leaves a handwritten note\non the desk for his successor"},{"time":1148375,"text":"that walks in a couple of hours later."},{"time":1150500,"text":"If you had to write such a note\nto your successor, Filippo Grandi,"},{"time":1153709,"text":"what would you write?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1154885,"text":"AG: Well, I don't think\nI would write any message."},{"time":1157973,"text":"You know, one of the terrible things\nwhen one leaves an office"},{"time":1160972,"text":"is to try to become the backseat driver,"},{"time":1163726,"text":"always telling the new one what to do."},{"time":1166637,"text":"So that, I will not do."},{"time":1168177,"text":"If I had to say something to him,"},{"time":1170145,"text":"it would be, \"Be yourself,\nand do your best.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1172753,"text":"BG: Commissioner, thank you\nfor the job you do."},{"time":1175023,"text":"Thank you for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1176552,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}